# Pin line endings so a core.autocrlf=true checkout (Git for Windows' suggested
# default) cannot produce CRLF working copies of files whose byte content matters:
# install.sh's anchor block handling compares text across runs, and *.sh must be
# LF to run under sh at all. (Gate finding, 0.2.1.)
* text=auto
*.sh text eol=lf
*.py text eol=lf
anchor/anchor.md text eol=lf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf
